{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bc397133-e1d4-4bca-86af-97b7b885a6cd","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform` package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (in a `<PropertyGroup>`):\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n4. **Optionally** enable the new output (recommended):\n   ```xml\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n\nAfter this, `dotnet test` will use Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest. Your test code itself doesn't need to change.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n| Before | After |\n|--------|-------|\n| `xunit.runner.visualstudio` | `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform` |\n| (none) | `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` |\n| (optional) | `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` |\n\nWould you like me to make these changes to a specific `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"779d2f32-282a-4e7b-bc98-b0d9e34bb408","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"9C4B:38EE64:150188F:179A359:69F86106"},"id":"2c5fe873-433f-4230-a125-6f160ea723d7","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:04:16.619Z","parentId":"b1184b01-1c5e-451a-bfa2-aef7c92e1665"}
